data.scripting-the-hooking#Scripting the hook:
Now the server is running, let’s write our script.
The documentation is easy to understand, so to hook a function we do :
const classWeWant = Java.use('package.classname'); classWeWant.methodName.implementation = function () { // whatever we want here } Let’s see if the message changes with this script, as it hooks the 3 anti root protection functions :
/// import Java from "frida-java-bridge"; import { log } from "./logger.js"; Java.perform(() => { const cClass = Java.use('sg.vantagepoint.a.c'); cClass.a.implementation = function () { return false; } cClass.b.implementation = function () { return false; } cClass.c.implementation = function () { return false; } }) We can use this command
